# https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#additionalAbility
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#additionalAbility> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#additionalAbility> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subPropertyOf> <https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#hasDivergence> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#hasDivergence> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#additionalAbility> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#Interpretation> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#additionalAbility> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#Ability> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#additionalAbility> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Links a source-specific Interpretation to an Ability that the creature possesses in that Source but which is absent from or not part of its standard biological description (Creature). Records additions to the creature's standard behavioural repertoire introduced by a specific author, artist, or tradition — e.g. a serpent that in one source is additionally credited with the power of hypnosis."@en .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#additionalAbility> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> <https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#SymbolicModule> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#additionalAbility> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "additional ability"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#additionalPart
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#additionalPart> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#additionalPart> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subPropertyOf> <https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#hasDivergence> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#additionalPart> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#Interpretation> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#additionalPart> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#AnatomicalPart> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#additionalPart> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Links a source-specific Interpretation to an AnatomicalPart that the creature possesses in that Source but which is not part of its canonical morphology. Records additive anatomical divergences introduced by a specific tradition — e.g. a lion that in one illumination is given wings absent from the standard description, shifting it toward a composite or hybrid morphology."@en .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#additionalPart> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> <https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#SymbolicModule> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#additionalPart> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "additional part"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#alternativeDiet
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#alternativeDiet> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#alternativeDiet> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subPropertyOf> <https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#hasDivergence> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#alternativeDiet> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#Interpretation> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#alternativeDiet> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#Diet> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#alternativeDiet> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Records a diet attributed to a creature in a specific interpretation that departs from its canonical diet, documenting how a particular source or tradition reimagines what the creature consumes. It captures source-specific dietary divergence at the level of the individual interpretation."@en .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#alternativeDiet> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> <https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#SymbolicModule> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#alternativeDiet> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "alternative diet"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#alternativeHabitat
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#alternativeHabitat> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#alternativeHabitat> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subPropertyOf> <https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#hasDivergence> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#alternativeHabitat> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#Interpretation> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#alternativeHabitat> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#Habitat> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#alternativeHabitat> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Records a habitat attributed to a creature in a specific interpretation that departs from its canonical habitat, documenting how a particular source or tradition relocates the creature. It captures source-specific habitat divergence at the level of the individual interpretation."@en .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#alternativeHabitat> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> <https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#SymbolicModule> .
