<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#embodiesArchetype> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Links a source-specific Interpretation to the universal psychological pattern or primordial image that the creature instantiates. Where :hasNarrativeFunction captures what role the creature plays in a given text, :embodiesArchetype asserts what deep collective structure it expresses across all its manifestations — e.g. the Dragon as the Archetype of Chaos, the Phoenix as the Archetype of Renewal, the Unicorn as the Archetype of Purity."@en .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#embodiesArchetype> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> <https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#SymbolicModule> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#embodiesArchetype> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "embodies archetype"@en .
