# 
# https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#extractedFrom
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#extractedFrom> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#extractedFrom> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#Citation> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#extractedFrom> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#Source> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#extractedFrom> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Links a Citation to the Source from which its passage was drawn. Where :hasTextualReference connects an Interpretation to a Citation, :extractedFrom connects that Citation upward to the Source document — completing the three-level provenance chain: Interpretation → Citation → Source. This property allows the ontology to answer questions such as 'which Sources contain direct textual evidence for this creature' by traversing the chain rather than asserting a direct link between Interpretation and Source."@en .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#extractedFrom> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> <https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#ProvenanceModule> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#extractedFrom> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "extracted from"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#habitatCategory
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#habitatCategory> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#habitatCategory> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#Habitat> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#habitatCategory> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#Habitat> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#habitatCategory> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Assigns a specific habitat to its broader environmental class, grouping particular places under a general category (such as Aquatic). It provides the higher-level classification through which individual habitats are organised."@en .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#habitatCategory> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> <https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#BiologicalModule> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#habitatCategory> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "habitat category"@en .
