<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#hasAbility> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> <https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#BiologicalModule> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#hasAbility> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "has ability"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#hasAbsenceOf
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#hasAbsenceOf> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#hasAbsenceOf> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subPropertyOf> <https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#hasAnomaly> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#hasAbsenceOf> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#RealAnimal> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#hasAbsenceOf> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#AnatomicalPart> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#hasAbsenceOf> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Indicates that a real animal, in a given Source or Interpretation, is missing an anatomical part that would normally be expected for its species. Records cases where the absence itself constitutes the anomaly — e.g. a serpent without a tongue, a bird without wings, or a humanoid creature lacking a face. Subproperty of :hasAnomaly."@en .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#hasAbsenceOf> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> <https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#BiologicalModule> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#hasAbsenceOf> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "has absence of"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#hasAnomaly
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#hasAnomaly> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#hasAnomaly> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#RealAnimal> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#hasAnomaly> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#AnatomicalPart> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#hasAnomaly> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Links a RealAnimal to an AnatomicalPart that exhibits a monstrous or pathological irregularity in a specific Source. For cases where the nature of the anomaly itself needs to be documented (e.g. whether it is a duplication, absence, or modification), use the subproperties :hasDuplicationOf, :hasAbsenceOf, and :hasModificationOf."@en .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#hasAnomaly> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> <https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#BiologicalModule> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#hasAnomaly> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "has anomaly"@en .
# 
