<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#hasModificationOf> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Indicates that a real animal, in a given Source or Interpretation, exhibits an anatomical part in an altered or aberrant form — neither simply absent nor duplicated, but substantially changed in shape, size, material, or function. Examples include reversed feet, crystalline horns, or scales in place of fur. Subproperty of :hasAnomaly."@en .
