<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#hasNarrativeFunction> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Links a source-specific Interpretation to the symbolic or thematic role that the creature fulfills within that Source. Unlike :embodiesArchetype — which asserts a universal psychological identity — :hasNarrativeFunction captures the contextual, plot-level, or iconographic function the beast performs in a particular text or artwork: guardian, omen, divine messenger, embodiment of sin, etc. The same creature may carry different narrative functions across different Interpretations."@en .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#hasNarrativeFunction> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> <https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#SymbolicModule> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#hasNarrativeFunction> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "has narrative function"@en .
