<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#hasOriginContext> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Links a creature or an imaginary place to their earliest known or most culturally foundational source, whether a specific written text or a broader mythological tradition. This property acknowledges that for many creatures a single primary source cannot always be identified."@en .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#hasOriginContext> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> <https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#ProvenanceModule> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#hasOriginContext> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "has origin context"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#hasPart
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#hasPart> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#hasPart> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#ImaginaryBeing> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#hasPart> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#AnatomicalPart> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#hasPart> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Links an ImaginaryBeing to a specific AnatomicalPart that constitutes its body, without asserting the biological origin of that part. Where :hasPartDerivedFrom links a CompositeCreature to the real animal or material from which a part originates, :hasPart simply records which anatomical components are present — useful for imaginary beings whose parts have no clear real-world derivation or whose source is not documented in the available sources."@en .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#hasPart> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> <https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#BiologicalModule> .
