<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#isTextualReferenceOf> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "The inverse of :hasTextualReference. Links a Citation back to the Interpretation it documents, allowing navigation from a specific passage in a Source to the interpretive claim it supports. This inverse direction is useful for querying which interpretations are grounded in a particular passage — for example, retrieving all creature readings that depend on a single chapter of a bestiary."@en .
