<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#relatedTo> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A symmetric associative property linking two NarrativeFunction or Archetype individuals that share thematic, structural, or symbolic overlap without one being a specialisation of the other. For example, the function of Guardian and the function of Threshold-Keeper are related but distinct; the Archetype of the Devourer and the Archetype of the Transformer share symbolic territory without subsumption. This property enables lateral navigation across the symbolic vocabulary of the ontology."@en .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#relatedTo> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> <https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#SymbolicModule> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#relatedTo> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "related to"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#removedAbility
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#removedAbility> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#removedAbility> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subPropertyOf> <https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#hasDivergence> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#removedAbility> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#Interpretation> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#removedAbility> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#Ability> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#removedAbility> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Links a source-specific Interpretation to an Ability that the creature typically possesses but which is deliberately absent in that particular Source. Documents reductive divergences from the standard behavioural description — e.g. a dragon that in a given medieval text lacks the ability to fly, inverting the conventional image."@en .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#removedAbility> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> <https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#SymbolicModule> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#removedAbility> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "removed ability"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#removedPart
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#removedPart> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#removedPart> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subPropertyOf> <https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#hasDivergence> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#removedPart> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#Interpretation> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#removedPart> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#AnatomicalPart> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#removedPart> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Links a source-specific Interpretation to an AnatomicalPart  that the Creature canonically possesses but which is deliberately absent or suppressed in that particular Source. Documents reductive anatomical divergences — e.g. a griffin depicted without its eagle wings in a specific manuscript tradition, fundamentally altering its composite identity."@en .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#removedPart> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> <https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#SymbolicModule> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#removedPart> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "removed part"@en .
