# 
# https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#hasPassageText
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#hasPassageText> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#DatatypeProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#hasPassageText> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#Citation> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#hasPassageText> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#Literal> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#hasPassageText> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "The transcribed text of the passage extracted from a Source in which a creature is described, named, or depicted. Stored as a plain literal, this property preserves the exact wording of the primary source evidence that grounds a given Interpretation, enabling philological comparison across different textual witnesses of the same creature."@en .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#hasPassageText> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> <https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#ProvenanceModule> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#hasPassageText> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "has passage text"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#hasPersonalName
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#hasPersonalName> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#DatatypeProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#hasPersonalName> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#Interpretation> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#hasPersonalName> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#Literal> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#hasPersonalName> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Records the proper name given to a creature in a specific interpretation, distinguishing a named individual from the generic species to which it belongs. It applies at the level of the interpretation, since a personal name is typically conferred by a particular source rather than shared across all manifestations of the creature."@en .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#hasPersonalName> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> <https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#ProvenanceModule> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#hasPersonalName> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "has personal name"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#hasRootTerm
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#hasRootTerm> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#DatatypeProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#hasRootTerm> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#Etymology> .
