<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#hasRootTerm> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "The literal string representation of the original word."@en .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#hasRootTerm> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> <https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#ProvenanceModule> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#hasRootTerm> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "has root term"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#hasSequenceIdentifier
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#hasSequenceIdentifier> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#DatatypeProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#hasSequenceIdentifier> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subPropertyOf> <http://purl.org/spar/fabio/hasSequenceIdentifier> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#hasSequenceIdentifier> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#Citation> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#hasSequenceIdentifier> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#Literal> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#hasSequenceIdentifier> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "The specific locator identifying the position of a Citation within its Source — such as a page number, folio reference, chapter, canto, stanza, or verse. Declared as a subproperty of fabio:hasSequenceIdentifier, aligning the ontology with the FRBR-aligned bibliographic vocabulary. This property allows precise scholarly referencing and enables the comparison of how different editions or translations of the same work locate their creature passages differently."@en .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#hasSequenceIdentifier> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> <https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#ProvenanceModule> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#hasSequenceIdentifier> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "has sequence identifier"@en .
