# 
# https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#Interpretation
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#Interpretation> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#Interpretation> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A specific conceptualization, reading, or artistic depiction of a creature as conceived by a particular creator within a specific Source. It distinguishes the universal concept of a Creature from its specific variations, allowing researchers to document how a single beast's anatomy, behavior, or allegorical meaning mutates when handled by different authors, artists, or historical periods."@en .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#Interpretation> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> <https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#ProvenanceModule> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#Interpretation> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Interpretation"@en .
