# https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#NarrativeFunction
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#NarrativeFunction> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#NarrativeFunction> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A symbolic or thematic role that a creature fulfills within a specific Source, independent of its biological traits. Narrative functions capture the cultural and literary work that a beast performs in a given tradition — e.g. acting as a guardian or an emblem of divine power. Where :Archetype captures the universal psychological pattern, NarrativeFunction captures the contextual, source-specific role that pattern takes within a narrative or iconographic programme."@en .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#NarrativeFunction> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> <https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#SymbolicModule> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#NarrativeFunction> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Narrative Function"@en .
