<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#ImaginarySymbol> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#inScheme> <https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#DurandImaginary> .
# 
# https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#IntimacySymbol
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#IntimacySymbol> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#NamedIndividual> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#IntimacySymbol> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#Concept> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#IntimacySymbol> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#ImaginarySymbol> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#IntimacySymbol> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#broader> <https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#MysticalStructure> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#MysticalStructure> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#NamedIndividual> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#IntimacySymbol> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#inScheme> <https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#DurandImaginary> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#IntimacySymbol> <https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#belongsTo> <https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#MysticalStructure> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#IntimacySymbol> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Intimacy symbol represents the center, the home, and the magical cradle. This symbol reduces the vast, terrifying world into a controllable, safe microcosm - such as a shell, a tomb seen as a place of rest, or a secret dwelling. It marks an inversion toward interiority and the soul, where the essence of the creature is protected within a restful and familiar space. It embodies the transition from the fear of being 'swallowed' to the comfort of being 'contained'."@en .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#IntimacySymbol> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> <https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#SymbolicModule> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#IntimacySymbol> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Intimacy Symbol"@en .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#IntimacySymbol> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel> "Intimacy Symbol"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#InversionSymbol
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#InversionSymbol> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#NamedIndividual> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#InversionSymbol> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#Concept> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#InversionSymbol> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#ImaginarySymbol> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#InversionSymbol> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#broader> <https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#MysticalStructure> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#InversionSymbol> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#inScheme> <https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#DurandImaginary> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#InversionSymbol> <https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#belongsTo> <https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#MysticalStructure> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#InversionSymbol> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Inversion symbol exorcises the fear of time by turning negative images into positive ones. Through an involutive process, the devouring mouth of the Diurnal Regime is transmuted into a protective nest. Instead of a heroic battle against darkness, there is a mystical union with it. This defensive mechanism employs doubling and reassuring symbols of intimacy to transform a dangerous fall into a controlled descent into the secrets of becoming."@en .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#InversionSymbol> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> <https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#SymbolicModule> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#InversionSymbol> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Inversion Symbol"@en .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#InversionSymbol> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel> "Inversion Symbol"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#LiteraryMetafiction
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#LiteraryMetafiction> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#NamedIndividual> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#LiteraryMetafiction> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#BestiaryType> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#LiteraryMetafiction> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A post-modern or highly stylized genre where the bestiary is used as a narrative or literary device (e.g. Borges)."@en .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#LiteraryMetafiction> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> <https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#ProvenanceModule> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#LiteraryMetafiction> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Literary Metafiction"@en .
