# https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#NyctomorphicSymbol
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#NyctomorphicSymbol> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#NamedIndividual> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#NyctomorphicSymbol> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#Concept> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#NyctomorphicSymbol> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#ImaginarySymbol> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#NyctomorphicSymbol> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#broader> <https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#SchizomorphicStructure> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#NyctomorphicSymbol> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#inScheme> <https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#DurandImaginary> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#NyctomorphicSymbol> <https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#belongsTo> <https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#SchizomorphicStructure> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#NyctomorphicSymbol> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Nyctomorphic symbol encapsulates the temporal symbolism of darkness, blindness, and shadows. Linked to the voracity of the night, it often incorporates the element of water - viewed here not as a source of life, but as an elusive, dark surface that doubles the abyss and reflects the formless terror of the unknown."@en .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#NyctomorphicSymbol> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> <https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#SymbolicModule> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#NyctomorphicSymbol> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Nyctomorphic Symbol"@en .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#NyctomorphicSymbol> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel> "Nyctomorphic Symbol"@en .
