# https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#SpectacularSymbol
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#SpectacularSymbol> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#NamedIndividual> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#SpectacularSymbol> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#Concept> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#SpectacularSymbol> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#ImaginarySymbol> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#SpectacularSymbol> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#broader> <https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#SchizomorphicStructure> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#SpectacularSymbol> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#inScheme> <https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#DurandImaginary> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#SpectacularSymbol> <https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#belongsTo> <https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#SchizomorphicStructure> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#SpectacularSymbol> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Spectacular symbol relates to intense light, vision, and the heroic gaze. Standing in direct opposition to darkness, it emphasizes the triumph of clarity and the 'solar power' that makes the world intelligible and thus controllable. Sight is the supreme sense of the hero, as clear vision allows for the differentiation of things and the definition of clear boundaries. In this context, light functions as a sword, cutting through obscurity to define reality."@en .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#SpectacularSymbol> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> <https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#SymbolicModule> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#SpectacularSymbol> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Spectacular Symbol"@en .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#SpectacularSymbol> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel> "Spectacular Symbol"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#SymbolicModule
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#SymbolicModule> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#NamedIndividual> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#SymbolicModule> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#Module> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#SymbolicModule> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "The Symbolic Module represents the analytical and interpretive layer of the ontology, where art history, literary theory, depth psychology, and anthropology converge. It provides two interlocking frameworks for the symbolic analysis of creatures and their source-specific Interpretations. First, the DurandImaginary scheme applies Gilbert Durand's anthropological structures of the imaginary to classify creatures according to the Regime (Diurnal or Nocturnal) and structural logic (Schizomorphic, Mystical, or Synthetic) that governs their symbolic imagery. Second, the archetype and narrative function layer — through :Archetype, :NarrativeFunction, :embodiesArchetype, and :hasNarrativeFunction — distinguishes between the universal psychological pattern a creature instantiates across all its manifestations and the specific contextual role it performs within a given Source. The module also captures symbolic divergences at the level of Interpretation: the properties :additionalPart, :removedPart, :additionalAbility, :removedAbility, :alternativeDiet and :alternativeHabitat document how a specific author or tradition departs from the canonical image of a creature, and what symbolic meaning those departures carry."@en .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#SymbolicModule> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Symbolic Module"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#SyntheticStructure
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#SyntheticStructure> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#Concept> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#SyntheticStructure> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#broader> <https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#ImaginaryStructure> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#SyntheticStructure> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#inScheme> <https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#DurandImaginary> .
# 
# https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#TeriomorphicSymbol
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#TeriomorphicSymbol> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#NamedIndividual> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#TeriomorphicSymbol> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#Concept> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#TeriomorphicSymbol> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#ImaginarySymbol> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#TeriomorphicSymbol> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#broader> <https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#SchizomorphicStructure> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#TeriomorphicSymbol> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#inScheme> <https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#DurandImaginary> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#TeriomorphicSymbol> <https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#belongsTo> <https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#SchizomorphicStructure> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#TeriomorphicSymbol> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Teriomorphic symbol represents the terrifying aspect of animals, embodying biting, devouring, and feral chaos. As 'enemy symbol' of anxiety and darkness, it is linked to the restlessness caused by rapid, undisciplined movement. It captures the chaos of fleeing from 'devouring time' and the archetype of the predatory jaws ready to strike."@en .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#TeriomorphicSymbol> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> <https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#SymbolicModule> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#TeriomorphicSymbol> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Teriomorphic Symbol"@en .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#TeriomorphicSymbol> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel> "Teriomorphic Symbol"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#Terrestrial
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#Terrestrial> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#NamedIndividual> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#Terrestrial> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#RealWorldPlace> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#Terrestrial> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A physical habitat primarily located on solid ground or within the earth."@en .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#Terrestrial> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> <https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#BiologicalModule> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#Terrestrial> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Terrestrial"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#hasDistinctiveTrait
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#hasDistinctiveTrait> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#NamedIndividual> .
<https://w3id.org/beast/ontology#hasDistinctiveTrait> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
